The United Nations tribunal
investigating the 2005 killing of former Lebanese Prime Minister
 Rafiq Hariri  appointed Judge Sir David Baragwanath as President
of the Tribunal and Presiding Judge of the Appeals Chamber, the
court said today in an e-mailed statement.  The appointment follows the resignation of Judge Antonio
Cassese yesterday, on health grounds, the tribunal said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
